Street Warfare 3

by: Sasanka Pallek

This game was made for my level 2 project at The League of Amazing Programmers.
Click here to download and play!

1. Why I Made This Game

I decided to make this game because I played a lot of similar games online as a kid. It brings back your childhood memories of playing 2D shooter games.

2. What I Learned

I learned ways to increase the performance and optimize overall. And even found a way to enhance the animation of movements.

3. Architecture of My Game

The game has three menus. One for the start, one for when you complete a wave, and one for game over. Plus, there is a small pop-up menu to see the controls of the game. The character has two modes, one for offensive and one for defensive. The offensive mode is when the character is equipped with a gun while the offensive is when a shield is equipped instead. The enemy fire can be deflected with your shield. But if offensive is your style, then you can take out enemies with your gun.

4. Technical Implementation

There are 8 total classes. And the main runner class creates and runs all the objects necessary. The object manager class manages all the objects like the enemies and the player character. While, the game panel class creates and runs manager object along with the soldier character. Each character class like the soldier, takes an image, and has each control movement methods.

5. Most Challenging Part

The most challenging part was figuring out how to make the soldier equip the shield that he could deflect bullets with. In order to do that I had to find a way to change the character image to one where he was holding a shield and then code so that if the bullet hit while in that image,it deflect.

6. Future Fixes and Updates

I would like to make the character seem like walking instead of dragging. But to do this I will need to figure out a way to make two images loop as I move the character forward or backward. Each image with the feet in different positions.
